HELLSCREAM looked at HYDRAS clearly getting exasperated. &quot;I don&#39;t know
everything he knew. I can only tell you he came back to the Earth to
try and strip it of whatever was left.&quot;

THRUSTOR shrugged, &quot;After the humans were almost wiped out by our
battles with the Autobots and Maximals the Earth really hasn&#39;t been
that good for us any more. We really doon&#39;t know why he came back.&quot;

Now the history that THRUSTOR and HELLSCREAM spoke of was NOT the
history that HYDRAS knew. In HYDRAS&#39; world, the EARTH was still a
blue/green planet filled with humans ready for the crushing, full of
mineral and energy resources that still be taken. It was not this ball
of rusting dust that he was seeing now.

It would look like here the war between the AUTOBOTS and DECEPTICONS
never truely stopped and the PAX CYBERTRONIA had not restored peace to
CYBERTRON. From the looks of things the MAXIMAL UPGRADE happened, but
so many other things were different. Like the EARTH here in this
universe was largely a war torn world.

Something was very very wrong. It was as if HYDRAS were in a different
universe, where the things of his universe had not happened here.
Where ever he was, he was not home.

